@@ -0,0 +1,120 @@
+# lib/import
+
+Build-URL importer subsystem for d4-tools.
+
+Translates shared build-planner URLs from community sites into saved
+`Character` + `Build` + equipped `Item`s in d4-tools.
+
+## Public surface
+
+Only one function is exported per importer:
+
+```typescript
+import { importMaxrollPlanner } from "@/lib/import/maxroll";
+// or via the top-level re-export:
+import { importMaxrollPlanner } from "@/lib/import";
+```
+
+No internal helpers (parser, fetcher, mapper, slot-map) are exported.
+
+## Maxroll importer (`lib/import/maxroll/`)
+
+Turns a Maxroll planner reference into a mapped character + build.
+
+### Accepted input shapes
+
+| Input | Example |
+|-------|---------|
+| Bare planner id | `abc123` |
+| Planner URL | `https://maxroll.gg/d4/planner/abc123` |
+| Planner URL with variant hash | `https://maxroll.gg/d4/planner/abc123#2&equipment` |
+| Build-guide URL | `https://maxroll.gg/d4/build-guides/frozen-orb-sorcerer` |
+
+### Usage
+
+```typescript
+import { importMaxrollPlanner, type ImportResult } from "@/lib/import/maxroll";
+
+const result: ImportResult = await importMaxrollPlanner("abc123");
+
+if (result.ok) {
+  // All variants returned — pick the one you want
+  const variant = result.variants[result.defaultVariantIndex];
+  console.log(variant.character.class);       // "Sorcerer"
+  console.log(variant.character.equippedItems); // Record<slot, Item>
+  console.log(variant.report.unmappedAffixes);  // structured report
+} else {
+  console.error(result.reason, result.message);
+}
+```
+
+### ImportContext (optional overrides)
+
+```typescript
+const result = await importMaxrollPlanner("abc123", {
+  fetch: myCustomFetch,    // default: globalThis.fetch
+  cacheDir: "/tmp/cache",  // default: DATA_DIR/maxroll-cache
+  now: new Date(),         // default: new Date()
+});
+```
+
+### data.min.json caching
+
+The Maxroll game-data catalog (`data.min.json`) is cached at
+`DATA_DIR/maxroll-cache/data.min.<patch>.json`. Cache is invalidated only
+when the catalog patch changes (no sliding TTL). Delete the file to force
+a re-fetch.
+
+### Env-var endpoint overrides
+
+| Variable | Default |
+|----------|---------|
+| `MAXROLL_PLANNER_API_BASE` | `https://planners.maxroll.gg` |
+| `MAXROLL_DATA_BASE` | `https://assets-ng.maxroll.gg` |
+
+### Report shape
+
+Every unmapped reference is captured in a per-category bucket (never
+silently dropped):
+
+```typescript
+report.unmappedAffixes     // { category: 'affix', nid, bnetFileName?, slot }[]
+report.unmappedAspects     // { category: 'aspect', nid, bnetFileName?, slot }[]
+report.unmappedParagonNodes // { category: 'paragon-node', nid, bnetFileName? }[]
+report.unmappedGlyphs      // { category: 'glyph', nid, bnetFileName?, boardNid }[]
+report.unmappedSkills      // { category: 'skill', nid, bnetFileName? }[]
+report.versionMismatch?    // present when data.min version ≠ catalog patch but mapping ≥ 50%
+```
+
+### Failure reasons
+
+| Reason | HTTP status (preview route) | Meaning |
+|--------|-----------------------------|---------|
+| `not-found` | 404 | Planner id doesn't exist |
+| `private` | 403 | Planner is private |
+| `patch-mismatch` | 409 | data.min version drifted AND < 50% explicits mapped |
+| `zero-mapped` | 422 | No items could be mapped |
+| `network` | 502 | Upstream fetch failed |
+| `parse-error` | 400 | Bad input or unexpected payload shape |
+
+## Server adapter
+
+`POST /api/import/maxroll/preview` — stateless, returns all variants in
+one response. The UI then commits the chosen variant via the existing
+`POST /api/characters?withDefaultBuild=true` endpoint.
+
+## UI
+
+`/import/maxroll` — four-state flow (paste → preview → confirm → redirect).
+Entry points: cmd-K → "Import Build from Maxroll planner…", Builds list
+page, New Character page.
+
+## Testing
+
+Hermetic Vitest suite at `__tests__/maxroll-import.test.ts` using
+checked-in fixtures:
+
+- `__tests__/fixtures/maxroll-planner-fixture.json` — Sorcerer build with 2 variants
+- `__tests__/fixtures/maxroll-data-min-subset.json` — minimal data.min covering referenced nids
+
+Run: `pnpm test -- --run __tests__/maxroll-import.test.ts`
